# sflow installation on your PC- 

1. Download the installer from thsi website - http://www.inmon.com/products/sFlowTrend.php#download
   I download linux installer. 
2. Copy the file to /bin folder. 
3. make it executable - 
   how to make a file executable - ? 
   $ chmod +x filename
   then you can run the file as $ ./filename
4. IT might ask for JAVA JVM to be installer. Go to this link and download - https://www.java.com/en/download/linux_manual.jsp
   I downloaded Linux64. 
5. INstall this - 
   1. Copy the download file into /usr/java - i dint have java folder so i created it. 
   2. untar this file - tar zxvf jre-8u73-linux-x64.tar.gz
   3. The Java files are installed in a directory called jre1.8.0_73 in the current directory. 
      In this example, it is installed in the /usr/java/jre1.8.0_73 directory. When the installation has completed, 
      you will see the word Done
6. Then be in root and run the sflow file - $ sudo bin/./sFlowTrend-unix-6_6.sh
   Its important to be in root else it wont execute. 